trans-unit.source: Obtains the MIDI file format of the input stream provided.

Obtains the MIDI file format of the input stream provided. The stream must point to valid MIDI file data. In general, MIDI file readers may need to read some data from the stream before determining whether they support it. These parsers must be able to mark the stream, read enough data to determine whether they support the stream, and, if not, reset the stream's read pointer to its original position. If the input stream does not support this, this method may fail with an IOException.

Estos analizadores deben poder marcar el flujo, leer suficientes datos para determinar si son compatibles con el flujo y, en caso contrario, restablecer el puntero de lectura del flujo a su posición original. Si el flujo de entrada no lo admite, este método puede fallar con una IOException .

Obtains the approximate maximum number of lines of the requested type that can be open simultaneously on the mixer. Certain types of mixers do not have a hard bound and may allow opening more lines. Since certain lines are a shared resource, a mixer may not be able to open the maximum number of lines if another process has opened lines of this mixer. The requested type is any line that matches the description in the provided Line.Info object. For example, if the info object represents a speaker port, and the mixer supports exactly one speaker port, this method should return 1. If the info object represents a source data line and the mixer supports the use of 32 source data lines simultaneously, the return value should be 32. If there is no limit, this function returns AudioSystem.NOT_SPECIFIED.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el número máximo aproximado de líneas del tipo solicitado que se pueden abrir simultáneamente en el mezclador. Ciertos tipos de mezcladores no tienen un límite rígido y pueden permitir abrir más líneas. Dado que ciertas líneas son un recurso compartido, es posible que un mezclador no pueda abrir el número máximo de líneas si otro proceso ha abierto líneas de este mezclador. El tipo solicitado es cualquier línea que coincida con la descripción del objeto Line.Info proporcionado . Por ejemplo, si el objeto de información representa un puerto de altavoz y el mezclador admite exactamente un puerto de altavoz, este método debería devolver 1. Si el objeto de información representa una línea de datos de origen y el mezclador admite el uso de 32 líneas de datos de origen simultáneamente, el el valor de retorno debe ser 32. Si no hay límite, esta función devuelve AudioSystem.NOT_SPECIFIED .

trans-unit.source: Obtains the current position in the audio data, in microseconds.

Obtains the current position in the audio data, in microseconds. The microsecond position measures the time corresponding to the number of sample frames captured by, or rendered from, the line since it was opened. The level of precision is not guaranteed. For example, an implementation might calculate the microsecond position from the current frame position and the audio sample frame rate. The precision in microseconds would then be limited to the number of microseconds per sample frame.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene la posición actual en los datos de audio,en microsegundos.La posición en microsegundos mide el tiempo correspondiente al número de cuadros de muestra capturados por la línea,o renderizados a partir de ella,desde que fue abierta.El nivel de precisión no está garantizado.Por ejemplo,una implementación podría calcular la posición de microsegundos a partir de la posición actual del cuadro y la velocidad de cuadro de la muestra de audio.La precisión en microsegundos se limitaría entonces al número de microsegundos por cuadro de muestra.

En su lugar, se recomienda utilizar getLongFramePosition .

trans-unit.source: Obtains the default Sequencer, connected to a default device.

trans-unit.source: One reason that a throwable may have a cause is that the class that throws it is built atop a lower layered abstraction, and an operation on the upper layer fails due to a failure in the lower layer. It would be bad design to let the throwable thrown by the lower layer propagate outward, as it is generally unrelated to the abstraction provided by the upper layer. Further, doing so would tie the API of the upper layer to the details of its implementation, assuming the lower layer's exception was a checked exception. Throwing a "wrapped exception" (i.e., an exception containing a cause) allows the upper layer to communicate the details of the failure to its caller without incurring either of these shortcomings. It preserves the flexibility to change the implementation of the upper layer without changing its API (in particular, the set of exceptions thrown by its methods).

A provider that does not support all the features required to construct an asynchronous file channel throws UnsupportedOperationException. The default provider is required to support the creation of asynchronous file channels. When not overridden, the default implementation of this method throws UnsupportedOperationException.

trans-unit.source: Opens or creates a file for writing, returning a BufferedWriter that may be used to write text to the file in an efficient manner.

Opens or creates a file for writing, returning a BufferedWriter that may be used to write text to the file in an efficient manner. The options parameter specifies how the file is created or opened. If no options are present then this method works as if the CREATE, TRUNCATE_EXISTING, and WRITE options are present. In other words, it opens the file for writing, creating the file if it doesn't exist, or initially truncating an existing regular-file to a size of 0 if it exists.
